Chelsea has finally agreed on a deal with RB Leipzig to sign striker, Timo Werner. The Blues confirmed this in a statement via its official website on Thursday. The statement reads: “Timo Werner has agreed personal terms with the Blues, and will remain at the German club for the rest of the Bundesliga season. “He will link up with his new team-mates in July, subject to passing a medical examination.” Werner has one of the most feared young strikers in Europe. The 24-year-old is renowned for his pace, movement, link-up play and finishing ability. He scored 32 goals and registered 13 assists in 43 appearances in all competitions for Leipzig.